flowRoot.flowPara: Place the card between the two players
Every player roll 6 dice, the player with most 6s is the first player, in case of tie, with most 5s, 4s...
The second player choose a die for the first player, don't change the die value.
The first player places the die chosen by the opponent in a free square on the card, there are no placement restrictions.
After placement: if a Trice is created the player who placed the die wins the game immediately or if a Double Trice is created he loses immediately.
If no Trice is created the player who placed the die chooses another die for the opponent and a new turn begins.
If the board is complete the player that place the last die must indicate a dice on the board, in the next turn the other player must swap the chosen die with one adjacent die.

After that he must increment the value of one of swapped dice by one (a 6 becomes 1), check if he make a Trice only after value change, in this case the game ends immediately. The game will continue with this rule untill a player make a Trice.
